<h3 id="duplicate-board-positions">Duplicate board positions</h3>
<p>The last thing I wanted to try was dealing with repeat positions. Previously I only skipped these if the same position occurred and they had same parent. But now I wanted to have a way of skipping board positions regardless of where they were in the game-tree. This took many hours to get correct, because in my first attempt caused the algorithm to produce sub-optimal moves.</p>

<p>The error was that when I pruned a board, I would finalise the boards value, despite the fact the board was not fully analysed. However, if the board occurs somewhere else in the tree, the analysis that was pruned can be relevant.</p>

